"The Best Christmas Ever" by James Patrick Kelly at the Wayback Machine (archived April 29, 2007): It was nominated for the 2005 Hugo Award for Best Short Story.[2] Plot summary: The story follows Albert Hopkins, the last real man on earth, and the biops that care for him. Granted his every wish, Albert is slipping into depression and the biops try everything to bring him out of it - including throwing a Christmas party that they think he will truly enjoy.

